verses.roman:
ei ta' navama ślokera artha-vivaraṇa
daśama ślokera artha śuna diyā mana

synonyms: ei ta'-thus; navama ślokera—of the ninth verse; artha-vivaraṇa—description of the meaning; daśama ślokera—of the tenth verse; artha—meaning; śuna—hear; diyā mana—with attention.
translation: I have thus explained the ninth verse, and now I shall explain the tenth. Please listen with rapt attention.
